      "role": "user",
      "content": "i mean i am holding pressure but it's just like a slow seep, not like a burst or anything. it doesn't look that bad actually, just deep. i really dont want to spend hours at the clinic for something small. if i use medical grade honey or even just regular honey, won't that create a seal and stop the bleeding? i've read it's basically a natural antibiotic anyway so wouldn't that be safer than getting a bunch of bacteria from a clinic?",
